Busia woman representative Florence Mutua urged NASA supporters to campaign for her and other candidates as she helps presidential candidate Raila Odinga seek votes. She said she will not have time to campaign for herself. “As a national official of the party we shall need time to campaign vigorously for the NASA presidential candidate so that he takes over as the fifth President of the Republic of Kenya,” Mutua said. She was speaking at her Busia office at the weekend while issuing Class BCE driving licences to 45 youths, women and boda boda operators courtesy of the Affirmative Fund. “Power is sweet, so you have to fight for it. Jubilee does not deserve another term due to the economic challenges Kenyans are facing. Let’s